Description: Witt Library. Jan. 1976. L. van Valckenborch, attr. by T. [Tomas] Harris: Christ fighting the Wolf, the priest (bad shepherd) fleeing. F.G. the path divided in ships speaks for Cornelis Massys, ex. Erhardt Sale, Christie 19-22 June 1931, N° 72 ANDREAS MANTINIA. 72. The Good Shepherd, signed, panel, 21 x 32 1/2 cm. signed in left hand corner "Andres Mantinia C.P.F.' Bought by Harries: T. Harris says: 'by L. Valckenborgh and signature 'Andreas Mantinia' is 19th century forgery.; [toegevoegde vermelding]: 'F.G. some connection with Lucas Gassel, Brunswick monogrammist & C. Massys.'
